Customer often move one issue to another issue type or project frequently. Although some constraint can be apply to the issue creation transition, it would not be applicable for the issue that being moved to the issue type or project.

User Use Case:

{quote}
We have used some settings to automatically change the assignee of an issue when it is created in JIRA, e.g. assign the issue to component lead for issue type "issuetypeA" or copy the value of the certain custom field to the field "assignee" for issue type "issuetypeB" through workflow configuration.

This works fine when we create issues in JIRA, but when we move issues from "issuetypeA" to "issuetypeB" by move issue function, the assignee remain the same as the original issue's, that means when we move the issue to another issue types, the assignee will not be changed as the auto-assign settings in JIRA.
{quote}

Suggestion:
Additional add a Move Issue Transition at the start of the workflow which same as Create Issue Transition. That would allow user to configure the constraint or condition of the issue that being move from one to another issue type or projects.

