For now, it is not possible to use the operator (~) when searching for projects. Because of this limitation, it is necessary to list all the project keys you want to search, even when the project keys are similar. For example, if you try to perform the following search: 

{noformat}
project in (TST,PRJ,JRA,GHS,CONF)
{noformat}

And you need to have this query for a great amount of projects (more than 100 sometimes), the JQL cannot handle that, as it has a limitation on the number of characters that can be used ( in our tests, the search limitation was a little over 2300 chars).

It would be really useful to perform searches on several projects in only one search.

For now, the workaround would be to split the search in multiple filters.

